{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7d1323bd-07a8-48ce-8c22-495cea39fb9b","content":"Two things change with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. `Category` trait → `category` (lowercase)\nMTP's filter engine is **case-sensitive** for trait names. xUnit v3 maps `[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]` but the filter key must be lowercase `category`.\n\n### 2. `&` operator → `&` or `and`\nThe `&` syntax still works, but the preferred MTP syntax uses parentheses and explicit operators for clarity.\n\n### Updated CI command\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests & category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nThe key fix is `Category` → **`category`** (lowercase `c`). In VSTest (v2) trait filtering was case-insensitive; in MTP it's case-sensitive, and xUnit v3 normalizes the trait name to lowercase.\n\nThe `FullyQualifiedName~` (contains) and `&` operator work the same way under MTP, so the rest of the filter is unchanged.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"49a648c3-54b3-4582-a2e6-e2addadeb9ef","outputTokens":249,"requestId":"67C3:2636C7:2B92C14:2FF0D37:69FD3729"},"id":"d4a3457f-d740-44ef-88d8-2dd38691edb1","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:06:57.207Z","parentId":"a928d177-cf13-4e36-91c2-146075cb4149"}
